http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Political-intervention-blamed-for-scholar%E2%80%99s-suicide/article14011933.ece

It is clear that circumstances created through political interventions led to the suicide of the University of Hyderabad research scholar Rohit Vemula, P.M. Kamalamma, member of the National Commission for Scheduled Castes (NCSC), has said. Talking to mediapersons here on Wednesday when she arrived for a NCSC sitting, Ms. Kamalamma, who hails from Andhra Pradesh, said the warring students had in fact settled their disputes.But the dispute was revived by political intervention, but for which the suicide would not have happened. She said that caste-based discrimination had worsened in educational institutions in the country.While all cases of atrocities against members of Scheduled Castes may not come before the NCSC, there was apprehension that such cases were increasing to alarming levels.